modules.description: This module handles WebSocket server connections by defining how to process incoming connections with custom response headers and byte handling logic. It works with `Websocket.t` connections, allowing the server to apply a deferred function to each connection for message processing. Concrete use cases include setting up WebSocket endpoints that require specific header configurations or custom asynchronous message handling workflows.

This module creates and manages WebSocket client connections with functions to establish a connection to a given URI and handle communication using specified message types. It works with URIs, HTTP headers, and WebSocket streams, supporting both text and binary message formats. Concrete use cases include connecting to real-time APIs, sending and receiving WebSocket messages, and ensuring proper resource cleanup after communication ends.

Handles WebSocket server connections with custom response headers and byte handling logic. Works with `Websocket.t` connections, applying deferred functions for asynchronous message processing. Enables setting up WebSocket endpoints requiring specific header configurations or custom subprotocol selection workflows.

This module implements WebSocket communication over HTTP using the Async library, handling both client and server connections with support for custom headers and subprotocols. It operates on WebSocket connections, HTTP requests and responses, and asynchronous streams, enabling real-time bidirectional messaging. Use cases include building WebSocket servers that process messages asynchronously and clients that connect to streaming APIs with precise header and protocol configurations.
